race.comment: HOT CHILLI MAMA (8) made progress last time out, finishing 3.5 lengths from the winner in third at the end of 1535m at Geelong after being in the firing line on the turn. Best figures measure up. Sure to run well. GINGER SWEET (10) doesn't win out of turn, scoring just once from 17 starts. Again tasted defeat last start when seventh over 1600m at Seymour, beaten 7 lengths. Perfectly placed and is sure to play a major role in this easier assignment. OLNEY (2) last appeared when he finished seventh over 2460m at Geelong on May 23 but can pull out a run fresh and is a winner at his only start here. EPICUS (5) is experiencing a long win drought, extended last start when sixth over 1200m at Hamilton after he was well back on straightening. Well placed and can run a better race. DOUGAL MCKEEN (3) ran an improved race last time out and from a draw that presents the rider with options, he'll get every chance to put up another strong performance.
